	   <tr><td colspan=2>I finally made my Trueshot at 12th level with a fletching skill of 155.&nbsp;&nbsp;Per all the wonderful advice on this site, I managed to make it on my 3rd try and have enough for 7 more tries, though I need to offload my initial Trueshot onto an alt for sakekeeping while I try to make others.  The best part about this, to my mind, is that after leveling up doing my newbie armor quests (Wood Elf Ranger), except for the darned gaunts, I started to hunt out the micro servos in Steamfont around about high 10th level and made decent experience getting me up to 12th by the time I had a full stack of servos.  The other great part about doing this at this level is that I was also hunting plague rats near the Steamfont windmills and the tails on those sell to the windmill merchants for 1 plat 6 gold and there is a fletcher merchant right there.  During any down time waiting for desired spawns or just healing/medding I also managed to increase my fletching skill, so I felt like I wasn't really wasting any time at all.  After hunting the servos (had the necessary spiderling silks from my newbie hunting days in the bank), I took the boat to Freeport and loaded up with about 15 small lanterns and several stacks of muffins.  Went to West Freeport to the second level of Hogcaller's Inn and found Jyle Windshot, handed in my lanterns and got my half stack of wood shards and the wood heart for the Rain Caller upgrade later on.  Since he was right in the hallway there as well, I decided to load up Pandos with muffins to increase my elf factions so now I'm warmly with most of the Kelethin folks, have to check Felwithe still, but better prices aren't a bad thing.  The apparently hairy part for many at this low a level is getting onto and off of Sister's Isle in OOT, but I admit this was a breeze for me, even without sow.  Just runn off the boat, before it comes to a complete stop, just so long as you hit the pier, run into the first hut slightly to the right of center, buy from the merchant immediately left inside.  I managed to buy 40 nuts (1 gp 8 sp each) and dash back to the boat with about 10 or 15 seconds to spare, easy.  Another thing that is pretty decent is that upon turning in the gathered materials to Maesyn Trueshot for the Treant Bow Staff, I got back between 15 and 18 gp; definitely not shabby.  I'll post a followup on further success and failure rates with the rest of my Trueshot materials.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
